            p.lead Farm to school provides economic development opportunities to producers (e.g., farmers, ranchers, fishers), laborers, distributors, processors, cooks and foodservice staff, as well as others who support the local food system. Farm to school activities can help build long-term economic vitality within a local food system by creating demand for local food products. Success in this sector is measured via local and regional economic impact, market opportunities, income generation, and social capital.
