            p.lead Farm to school activities can support practices that build healthy soil, clean air, clean water and ecosystem processes in urban, suburban and rural environments, while impacting participants' ecological ethics. Farm to school activities may also support environmentally sound, sustainable and just approaches to food production, processing, packaging, transportation and marketing. Success in this sector is measured via student and adult environmental literacy, environmentally friendly practices in schools, and support for sustainable food production methods and practices.
